caption: I truly adore Fuji East Japanese Bistro. The mood is really fun and the staff is remarkable. Each and every single thing that we ordered was incredibly fresh and flavorful. The staff was fantastic! Prompt service. I certainly recommend that spot!

We love supporting Fuji East Japanese Bistro as the local sushi spot on RI. The food is always super fresh, they are very accommodating with substitutes and very fast with both delivery and pickup orders. If you place your order with them directly, the prices are also considerably cheaper than 3rd party apps like Grubhub/Seamless!

I wouldn’t recommend this restaurant unless you’re desperate for sushi on Roosevelt island. Sushi at the Foodtown supermarket is cheaper and comparable. For the same price as Fuji, you can probably order delivery elsewhere and get better food. I also tried the fried rice and it was a bit tasteless. Maybe this place thinks they can overcharge since there’s no other similar restaurant close by but the food is not worth the prices at all.
Good food, great service, professional chefs
Love this place! Great sushi and service.
Great staff yummy sushi and great location
Not bad at all. And extremely convenient as well.

I’ve eaten at many Japanese restaurants and never came across something so bizarre. The food was below sub par and the person on phone was rude to talk to. Won’t be ordering here again.

This is not a proper Japanese restaurant, I ordered teriyaki beef and it came out like this. The taste is very bland.

It is not our first time here, we live on the island but I will not be back soon. Despite leaving a tip the waitress demanded more, 18% for being 5 people. When we asked if it was a recommendation, he showed us the carte stating that the tip for a group of 5 people is 18%. We ordered a lunch special each one (5) plus two à la carte dishes. The restaurant was almost empty, there was only one table with one person. Paying that 18% we pay a plate more of the carte, even more expensive than the lunch special. The food is fine but it is not so wonderful as to endure this to pay much more for being a family of 5 members.

I try to sample Shrimp Shumai wherever I go and find it available.   I generally have it steamed, and try it with its soy dip, and without.  For the price, I find it to be a little expensive, and the dumplings skin was thick for Shumai.  However,  the taste and dip where the best I've had so far.   They serve a relatively sweet Shumai and dip here.

We live in the same building as this restaurant and order at least once a month from here. The sushi is delicious and fresh. The dumplings and tempura are yummy. The miss soup is hearty and warming just as it should be. The atmosphere in the restaurant is lovely, it's a shame it isn't bigger but still very nice. In the summer, there's a small but pleasant outdoor area where you can eat with your dog. Everything is reasonably priced and most of the staff are very nice and polite. There is one grumpy woman though who served us the first time we came here, best to avoid her if possible! We had an hour until closing time, she reluctantly seated us, grumbled lots and rushed us through our whole meal though we were done in 45 mins. Also if getting takeout be wary, we think the meat/seafood overcooks as it sits waiting to be picked up. We've had overcooked beef, shrimp, salmon and tough chicken multiple times which is disappointing.

The rolls are great! The size, fish to rice ratio, quality--all excellent! Of all the places I've had sushi in the city, from cheap too expensive, this is the best! The seafood garlic noodle, tiger roll, and crispy duck roll are my favorite dishes. I'm disappointed any time I get sushi anywhere else after having Fuji East's food.  I don't know why I read a complaint about service, but the servers are all very pleasant and quick. You might not get big American style smiles and waitress small talk, unless you become a regular! They learn your orders (if you're like my family and order your favorite dishes every time from restaurants) and remember repeat customers.  Also in the summertime, the outdoor seating right on the lawn with views of the river and flowers is wonderful.

The sushi often has a fishy odor/taste and feel slimy. I have stopped eating half way through my meal several times when ordering here. We would only order here out of desperation if for some reason other sushi places on seamless are not delivering, and stick with noodles.

I've lived on Roosevelt Island for about 3 years now after moving up from Florida and by far this is one of the better sushi places in NYC. I've eaten at several dozen since I've lived here from super high end to the tiny hole in the walls and other than Fuji East, I've been disappointed in some aspect of every other place I've been. Either the portions are tiny or the quality of the fish is poor or the service is bad. Fuji fulfills all of those criteria very well. I honestly still like Seito Sushi in Orlando a little better but Fuji is an awesome gem on Roosevelt Island.  PS try the Spicy Girl Roll
